he also spearheaded the formulation of a new school of earth and space exploration combining earth planetary and astrophysical sciences with systems engineering in a nationallyunique interdisciplinary academic unit in  leshin served on president bush’s commission on implementation of united states space exploration policy a ninemember commission charged with advising the president on the execution of his new vision for space exploration from  to  leshin was the director of sciences and exploration directorate at nasas goddard space flight center where she oversaw science activities from  to  she was the deputy center director for science  technology at goddard in this position she oversaw strategy development at the center leading an inclusive process to formulate future science and technology goals and an integrated program of investments aligned to meet those goals with other nasa goddard senior managers she was responsible for effectively executing the centers’ b in programs and ensuring the scientific integrity of earth observing missions spacebased telescopes such as the james webb space telescope and instruments exploring the sun moon mercury mars saturn comets and more starting in  leshin served as the deputy associate administrator for nasa’s exploration systems mission directorate where she played a leading role in nasas future human spaceflight endeavors her duties included oversight of the planning and execution of the next generation of human exploration systems as well as the research robotic and future capabilities development activities that support them she was also engaged in initiating the development of commercial human spaceflight capabilities to low earth orbit from  to  leshin served as dean of the school of science and professor of earth  environmental science at rensselaer polytechnic institute where she led the scientific academic and research enterprise leshin’s scientific expertise is in cosmochemistry and she is primarily interested in deciphering the record of water on objects in the solar system in february  president obama appointed her to the advisory board of the smithsonian national air and space museum and she was appointed by former secretary of transportation ray lahood to the advisory board of the us merchant marine academy she serves on the united states national research councils committee on astrobiology and planetary science and as chair of the advisory board for the thriving earth exchange of the american geophysical union in  leshin was named the th president of worcester polytechnic institute she has published approximately  scientific papers awardsedit leshin received the nasa distinguished public service medal in  for her work on the presidential commission and the outstanding leadership medal in  for her work at nasa in  she was the inaugural recipient of the meteoritical societys nier prize awarded for outstanding research in meteoritics or planetary science by a scientist under the age of  the international astronomical union recognized her contributions to planetary science with the naming of asteroid  leshin referencesedit  worcester polytechnic institute names laurie leshin as its th president office of marketing  communications at worcester polytechnic institute retrieved january    external linksedit rensselaer polytechnic institute school of science web page agu planetary sciences section web page laurie leshin’s profile in nasa exploration systems mission directorate web page tempe diablos success story laurie leshin v t e presidents of worcester polytechnic institute charles o thompson  homer t fuller  thomas c mendenhall  edmond a engler  ira n hollis  ralph earle  francis w roys acting  wat tyler cluverius jr  alvin e cormeny  arthur b bronwell  harry purnell storke  george w hazzard  edmund t cranch  jon strauss  edward alton parrish  dennis berkey  laurie leshin  retrieved from httpsenwikipediaorgwindexphptitlelaurieleshinoldid categories living peoplerensselaer pol